    "body": "## Problem\r\nPotential documentation drift in `tui.txt` if fields for `$NVIM_TERMDEFS` change.\r\n\r\n## Solution\r\nGenerate docs for `tui.txt`. Add `brief_xform` to `gen_vimdoc.lua` to allow transforming briefs during generation.\r\nAlso fixed some extra whitespace and alignment while I was at it. We were using two ways of aligning helptags, but now both places call the same function.\r\nThe helptags still aren't fully right-aligned to 78 chars if `conceallevel=2`. Not sure if that's desired, but it's an easy fix in `align_tags` if needed.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
