            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I think we aren't gaining much by moving this here. Instead, `gen_vimdoc.lua` has support for appending to help files, and that's how like `lua.txt` are generated.\n\nInserting stuff isn't really well-supported, so instead I suggested adding a new section at the end of `tui.txt`:\n\n```\n==============================================================================\nTerminfo override                                               *tui-termdefs*\n```\n\nand then append the generated part to that. Then the NVIM_TERMDEFS section can just point to it.",
            "commit_id": "22d8f2f6212f926495a892bb0d9b7768de549e3e",
            "created_at": "2026-05-18T13:20:56Z",
